raw_logic_programs:
Predicates:
SaladEater(x) ::: x eats salads regularly.
HealthConscious(x) ::: x is very conscious about their health and eating habits.
GrewUpHealthy(x) ::: x grew up in health-conscious childhood homes.
NutritionFulfilled(x) ::: x fulfills their nutritional daily intakes.
GoodParents(x) ::: x has good relationships with their parents.
GymVisitor(x) ::: x visits the gym at least once a day.
Premises:
∀x (SaladEater(x) → HealthConscious(x)) ::: All people who eat salads regularly are very conscious about their health and eating habits.
∀x (GrewUpHealthy(x) → SaladEater(x)) ::: All people who grew up in health-conscious childhood homes eat salads regularly.
∀x (NutritionFulfilled(x) → GrewUpHealthy(x)) ::: All people who fulfill their nutritional daily intakes grew up in health-conscious childhood homes.
∀x (GoodParents(x) → NutritionFulfilled(x)) ::: If people have good relationships with their parents, then they fulfill their nutritional daily intakes.
∀x (GoodParents(x) → ¬SaladEater(x)) ::: If people have good relationships with their parents, then they do not eat salads regularly.
∀x (GymVisitor(x) → NutritionFulfilled(x)) ::: If people visit the gym at least once a day, then they always fulfill their daily nutritional intakes.
(GrewUpHealthy(taylor) ∧ GoodParents(taylor)) ⊕ ¬(GrewUpHealthy(taylor) ∨ GoodParents(taylor)) ::: It is either both true that Taylor grew up in a health-conscious childhood home and she has a good relationship with her parents, or it is true that Taylor neither grew up in a health-conscious childhood home nor has a good relationship with her parents.
Conclusion:
SaladEater(taylor) ::: Taylor eats salads regularly.
